cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.LG. 

The paper focuses on developing a multimodal architecture for supporting robust continuous spoken dialog, which involves natural language processing, decision making under uncertainty, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), as well as statistical learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SD) for managing uncertainties.
